                            <comment id="13400895" author="mdodsworth@salesforce.com" created="Mon, 25 Jun 2012 21:03:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;all feedback/review comments welcome&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13401430" author="janhoy" created="Tue, 26 Jun 2012 14:32:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Great. Are you able to add a JUnit test which reproduces the bug and shows that it is fixed?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13401873" author="mdodsworth@salesforce.com" created="Wed, 27 Jun 2012 01:54:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;added test.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for looking at the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13402130" author="janhoy" created="Wed, 27 Jun 2012 10:47:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated trunk patch with extended test and CHANGES entry. Looks good to me. Any other comments before commit?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13402134" author="janhoy" created="Wed, 27 Jun 2012 11:03:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This was an easy backport for 3.6.1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13402287" author="mdodsworth@salesforce.com" created="Wed, 27 Jun 2012 15:14:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you, Jan.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From what I can tell, &apos;/&apos; only became a reserved character since 4.0 - &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2604&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2604&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13402910" author="janhoy" created="Thu, 28 Jun 2012 07:43:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yea, I see that. Actually, I cannot get the test to fail, even with 3.6.0 - is there a better way to trigger the missing escaping of particularly &apos;&amp;amp;&apos;, &apos;&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;&apos; and &apos;|&apos; ? If not, then I cannot see a need for a 3.6.x patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13402911" author="janhoy" created="Thu, 28 Jun 2012 07:45:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;New patch which also uncomments partialEscape() which is dead code&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13402946" author="janhoy" created="Thu, 28 Jun 2012 09:06:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Checked in to trunk and 4.x&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13405147" author="mdodsworth@salesforce.com" created="Mon, 2 Jul 2012 17:28:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;much appreciated, Jan. Thank you.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
